<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>It started with missing taskbar that I restored by deleting plasma-org.kde.plasma.desktop-appletsrcfrom ~/.config. I reapplied my visual settings from previous working setup step by step manually. It worked fine until next reboot, I started noticing this. I get this corrected by restarting plasma session running the following commands:</p> <p>kquitapp5 plasmashell</p> <p>kstart5 plasmashell</p> <p>However it defaults to this broken state after waking from sleep or reboot. To me it looks like KDE packages got corrupted in some way in the last update.</p> <p>I wonder if anybody faced this weird GUI issues before and found fix. I am considering downgrading Plasma to 5.24 LTS for more stability if that is available option.</p> <p>&#x200B;</p> <p><a href="https://ibb.co/sKTRNvj">Screenshot</a></p> <p>----------- <br/> OS: Arch Linux x86_64 <br/> Host: XPS 13 9305 <br/> Kernel: 5.18.14-arch1-1 <br/> Uptime: 24 mins <br/> Packages: 1330 (pacman) <br/> Shell: bash 5.1.16 <br/> Resolution: 2560x1440 <br/> DE: Plasma 5.25.3 <br/> WM: kwin <br/> WM Theme: McSur-dark <br/> Theme: [Plasma], Breeze [GTK3] <br/> Icons: McMojave-circle-dark [Plasma], McMojave-circle-dark [GTK2/3] <br/> Terminal: konsole <br/> CPU: 11th Gen Intel i5-1135G7 (8) @ 4.200GHz <br/> GPU: Intel TigerLake-LP GT2 [Iris Xe Graphics] <br/> Memory: 3276MiB / 7674MiB </p> <p>&#x200B;</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/ZD_plguy17"> /u/ZD_plguy17 </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/waylfn/plasma_desktop_broken_since_update_to_5253/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/waylfn/plasma_desktop_broken_since_update_to_5253/">[comments]</a></span>